        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 1:48AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 147 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
about 14 miles west of Eldorado, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The Intersection Of Ranch Road 1828 And Ranch Road 915, The
Intersection Of Us-190 And Ranch Road 1828, Eldorado, Us-
277 Near The Sutton-
Schleicher County Line, Adams, The Intersection Of Us-
190 And Ranch Road 2084, and I-10 Near The Crockett-
Sutton County Line.

This includes Interstate 10 in northwestern Sutton County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for west central
Texas.</instruction>
